body:
Currently, property definition with empty parentheses is not supported. For example, consider the following module.

``` SystemVerilog
module test (
    input clk,
    input rst,
    input tvalid
);

    property my_property_1;
        @(posedge clk) disable iff (rst) tvalid;
    endproperty

    property my_property_2();
        @(posedge clk) disable iff (rst) tvalid;
    endproperty

    sva_1: assert property(my_property_1()) else $error("assertion failed");
    sva_2: assert property(my_property_2()) else $error("assertion failed");

endmodule : test
```

This would result in such error

```
$ verilator --cc test.sv
%Error: test.sv:11:28: syntax error, unexpected ')', expecting IDENTIFIER or randomize
   11 |     property my_property_2();
      |                            ^
%Error: Internal Error: test.sv:1:8: ../V3ParseSym.h:124: Symbols suggest ending PROPERTY 'my_property_2' but parser thinks ending MODULE 'test'
    1 | module test (
      |        ^~~~
```

As specified in *IEEE Std 1800-2017, Annex A.2.10 Assertion declarations*, a `property_declaration` can has none or multiple `property_port_item` in its parentheses, so hopping such syntax can be supported by Verilator.
